│ 3162 /// VPRegionBlock represents a collection of VPBasicBlocks and VPRegionBlocks                                                          │
│ 3163 /// which form a Single-Entry-Single-Exiting subgraph of the output IR CFG.                                                            │
│ 3164 /// A VPRegionBlock may indicate that its contents are to be replicated several                                                        │
│ 3165 /// times. This is designed to support predicated scalarization, in which a                                                            │
│ 3166 /// scalar if-then code structure needs to be generated VF * UF times. Having                                                          │
